# Virtual environment
venv/

# Python cache
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd

# Environment variables (secrets!)
.env

# FAISS index files (large binary files)
*.index

# Uploaded PDFs
data/raw/*.pdf

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/

# Logs
logs/
*.log
```

**Why this matters:** The `venv/` folder can be 200MB+. You never commit it — you commit `requirements.txt` instead, so anyone can recreate the environment. The `.env` file will hold your API keys later. Committing secrets to GitHub is a career-limiting mistake.

